Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.88,0:00:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,brought him back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.01,0:00:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.59,0:00:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,brought that monster back to life...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.64,0:00:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.19,0:00:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You found something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.69,0:00:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald's library donation ceremony!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Tenma there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.82,0:00:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dieter, wait here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.28,0:00:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.83,0:00:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.91,0:00:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.13,0:00:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I think he's at the Munich University library...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.09,0:00:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,donating his collection of books today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.39,0:00:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go there immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma's target is Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.19,0:01:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.44,0:01:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lotte! You came!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.87,0:01:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I looked for him everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.99,0:01:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he doesn't seem to be here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.04,0:01:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though we've become friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's too bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.96,0:01:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.17,0:01:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are twins, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.01,0:01:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.55,0:01:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this picture book mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.64,0:01:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly collapsed when he saw this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.47,0:01:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A picture book...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.46,0:03:55.67,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Once upon a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.20,0:04:00.17,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,there lived a monster without a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.00,0:04:08.92,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster wanted a name so\Nbadly that he couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:15.87,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,So the monster decided to go off on\Na journey to find himself a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.51,0:04:20.68,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,But because the world was so big...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.89,0:04:25.68,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,the monster split in two and departed\N in their separate ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.77,0:04:28.22,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,One went east...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:31.23,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,and the other went west.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.15,0:04:37.23,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The one that went east found a village.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.44,0:04:41.74,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a blacksmith at the village entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.66,0:04:47.20,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mr. Blacksmith, please give me your name."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:49.33,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I can't give you my name."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.50,0:04:51.96,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you give me your name..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:56.79,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I will jump inside you and make\Nyou stronger in return."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.80,0:04:58.13,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"Really?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.13,0:05:01.55,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll give you my name if you can make me stronger."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:09.06,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster jumped inside the blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:14.27,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster became Otto the blacksmith.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.56,0:05:20.44,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Otto the blacksmith was the strongest man in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.44,0:05:21.28,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,But one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:25.53,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"Look at me! Look at me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.53,0:05:29.04,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"The monster inside me has grown this big!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:34.29,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Chomp. Munch. Crunch. Gulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:42.30,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The hungry monster ate Otto from the inside out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:48.26,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,He went back to being a monster without a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.52,0:05:53.18,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he jumped inside Hans the shoemaker...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:06:00.86,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Chomp. Munch. Crunch. Gulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.86,0:06:05.32,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,He went back to being a monster without a name again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.49,0:06:08.95,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he jumped inside Thomas the hunter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:15.00,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Chomp. Munch. Crunch. Gulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:19.34,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,He still went back to being a monster without a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.67,0:06:25.47,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster went to the castle to find a wonderful name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.47,0:06:35.02,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the castle, there was a very sick boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.56,0:06:41.27,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll make you stronger if you give me your name."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:46.53,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll give you my name if you can cure\Nmy illness and make me stronger."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.53,0:06:50.66,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster jumped inside the hoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:56.50,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The boy became very healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.33,0:06:59.88,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The king was delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:03.88,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"The prince is well! The prince is well!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.05,0:07:09.76,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster became fond of the boy's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:11.89,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,He also grew fond of his life inside the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.06,0:07:17.35,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he endured even when he became hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.35,0:07:22.52,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, even when his stomach\Nbecame very empty, he endured.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.52,0:07:25.90,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,But because he became so hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.99,0:07:29.95,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"Look at me! Look at me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.95,0:07:33.08,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"The monster inside me has grown this big!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.79,0:07:39.50,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The boy ate his father, his servants, and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:44.75,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Chomp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.51,0:07:46.51,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Munch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:48.42,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Crunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.38,0:07:50.84,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Gulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.60,0:07:55.68,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Because everyone was gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.43,0:07:58.52,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,the boy left on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.19,0:08:06.86,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,He walked and walked for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:13.95,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,One day...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.95,0:08:16.83,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,the boy met the monster that went west.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.29,0:08:21.00,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I have a name."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.00,0:08:23.38,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's a wonderful name."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.38,0:08:25.63,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the monster that went west said...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.55,0:08:28.84,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't need a name."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:31.18,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm happy even if I don't have a name."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.22,0:08:36.01,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,"Because we're monsters without names."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:42.73,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,The boy ate the monster that went west.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:47.11,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he now had a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:49.99,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,there was no one left to call him by his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:52.70,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.70,0:08:54.53,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a wonderful name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.14,0:09:02.96,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(382,0)\pos(360,341)}A Monster Without a Name
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.01,0:09:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know this picture book, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.34,0:09:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you read Czech?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Czech?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.93,0:09:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.69,0:09:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.73,0:09:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like someone read it to me... a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.07,0:09:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.16,0:09:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.87,0:09:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.83,0:09:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.26,0:09:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know? We're talking about you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.93,0:09:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you not know about yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.68,0:09:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.97,0:10:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I get such a bad feeling\Nwhen I read this picture book?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.90,0:10:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That student, Fahren, who claimed to be\NSchuwald's son, committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The detective Schuwald hired fell to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the prostitute who called herself\NMargot Langer was shot and killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that after reading this book, all\Nthe strange things happening recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,feel like they're merging together to crush me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.38,0:10:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I get the feeling that everything is tied to Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.17,0:10:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a little too agitated...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man who fainted after reading this book...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.60,0:10:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looks that much like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.19,0:10:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.99,0:10:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks so much like me that we could be twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This friend of yours, Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.87,0:11:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.79,0:11:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's attending a book donation ceremony\Nat the university library...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, h-hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.39,0:11:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, thanks to the efforts of the head\Nof the Schuwald financial group...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.98,0:11:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hans Georg Schuwald...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.53,0:11:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the University of Munich Friedrich Emmanuel\NSchool Library has been bestowed with...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.62,0:11:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an enormous collection of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are extremely important and precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can be said that this is Germany's most valuable asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.42,0:11:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have the responsibility to leave this...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.34,0:11:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,vast amount of human knowledge...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:11:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the younger generation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.23,0:12:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, a word from the head of the\NFriedrich Emmanuel School...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.98,0:12:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Steinbeck!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.88,0:12:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.01,0:12:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.80,0:12:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I pull the trigger...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.72,0:12:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everything will be over, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please move!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.89,0:12:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Help me, Doctor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.81,0:12:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't want to die!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.52,0:12:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doctor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.19,0:12:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Doctor!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.05,0:13:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Mauler!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.06,0:13:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:17.19,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, it's time for today's guest of honor to make his appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:21.21,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not only the essence of the Bayern economy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.86,0:14:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:25.34,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,but he also has great influence in Europe's economic development.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.71,0:14:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how you shoot a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.57,0:14:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And also, by donating his large collection\Nof books to the university...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he has done a great culturally\Nmeritorious service to Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.58,0:14:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take pride in being able to introduce this man to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.55,0:14:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen of the audience...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.55,0:14:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hans Georg Schuwald
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.18,0:14:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you shoot a gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.74,0:15:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you shoot a gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.01,0:15:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So many people have gathered here. What a success...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Schuwald is certainly popular...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And also, by donating his large collection\Nof books to the university...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.40,0:15:50.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he has done a great culturally\Nmeritorious service to Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.87,0:15:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take pride in being able to introduce this man to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.79,0:15:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen of the audience...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.79,0:16:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Hans Georg Schuwald
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.76,0:16:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one you're after is me, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.89,0:16:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are many people gathered here...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.27,0:17:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They came in droves to see you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.88,0:17:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.30,0:17:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What have you done...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.68,0:17:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, don't make any noise!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.56,0:17:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just shut up and watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.60,0:17:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.78,0:17:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I want you to listen to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.78,0:17:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to stay calm and act rationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.91,0:18:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how many people are gathered here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't all move at once...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.52,0:18:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.68,0:18:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch what I'm about to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.96,0:18:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Slowly, in single file...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.00,0:18:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,get away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.09,0:19:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.85,0:19:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.60,0:19:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A short circuit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.77,0:19:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the fire extinguisher!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.73,0:19:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.04,0:20:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.75,0:20:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My job was to shoot Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.84,0:20:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.97,0:20:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.97,0:20:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must've changed your mind Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is better!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.10,0:20:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is much better!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.39,0:20:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ants... They're all like ants running away from the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.86,0:20:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing! This is amazing, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.44,0:20:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is marvelous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.08,0:20:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take a look, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.31,0:21:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The books!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the books will burn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.90,0:21:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all running around...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.03,0:21:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're trampling one another, as if each\Nis more important than the rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.95,0:21:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you feel it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.66,0:21:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fear in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.88,0:21:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.22,0:21:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.18,0:21:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.39,0:21:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.22,0:21:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to... shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.64,0:21:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.23,0:21:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can only save life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taking life is my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.41,0:22:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:31.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(193,474)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(190,20)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:47.47,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(191,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(189,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:26.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(192,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.01,0:23:34.43,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:36.89,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.22,0:23:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
